Radio Button Java Code.

Now assume that we have to check that our radio button is checked when activity comes back to resume state, this approach then
helps to check whether that RadioButton is selected or not.
Also, as the Java approach is good rather than that onClick atttribute in the RadioButton Element(as that only works when the button clicked).

//Code.

RadioGroup radioGroup;

@Override
    protected void onResume() {
        super.onResume();
        
        radioGroup = findViewById(R.id.my_radio_group);//Assign your radioGroup id.
        boolean checked = ((RadioButton)radioGroup.findViewById(R.id.my_button)).isChecked();// Checking for particular button that it is checked or not.

        if(checked){
            Toast.makeText(getApplicationContext(),"Yes! it is checked", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
        }else{
            Toast.makeText(getApplicationContext(), "No, not checked", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
        }
    }
